I close with a consideration which is not without force for certain minds. Unless we know God in the Face of Jesus Christ we do not know Him at all. Nay, in that case, we know nothing for certain. You go to Nature for some conception of God. But Nature only illustrates and confirms the belief in God or the denial of God with which you approach her and examine her processeS. ’Tis a fine hour, indeed, the dawn‚ and it quickens the piety and hope of all honourable souls to see the sun burst fresh upon the world. But there is more than dawn in any day: there is twilight, there is darkness3 and if the morning brings joy to man’s soul, the night by the same law should bring despair.
